I don't care what "God says". Why? Because those men that supposedly
wrote the book wrote it because they felt moved to do so in their
hearts and minds and were "lead by God". Who is to say that I, myself,
am not lead by God? Who is to say that my heart, and my mind are not
directly connected to God in the same way as these men. Wouldn't God
tell me the same things that he told them? Following my own heart, from
what's right and wrong to what it is I'm supposed to do with my life...
as long as I am open, aware, and even listen?! Should I follow a book
that teaches many things that make me feel uneasy and uncomfortable and
goes against the natural instincts of humanity?

What kind of God would create beings, and then demand them to be better
than he created, and hold them accountable for that? Thats like
demanding a cat to walk on two legs at all times, or asking a dog to
meow and a Cheeseburger to be a HotDog.

