EternityGrace said "Who is to say that I, myself, am not lead by God?
Who is to say that my heart, and my mind are not
directly connected to God in the same way as these men. Wouldn't God
tell me the same things that he told them?"

Me: That's exactly correct, you could very well be all these things.
But if you are, you will not be breaking the laws of right living. You
will not be a living contradiction within yourself. You will not longer
say, as Paul once said about His pre-saved life, "the good I want to
do, I do not do". You will be whole, complete and empowered to do ALL
the good things you know that you should do. You will love, not hate
your enemies. You will give your cloak as well, to those who compel you
to give your shirt. You will resent not evil, but overcome it with a
good and proper attitude. You will be still within and know what is
right to do each and every moment and do it.

Not sinning does not mean you have suddenly become perfect...you may
still spill milk and choose the wrong answer on your drivers license
test, or even misunderstand what another says to you, but you will not
be divided within yourself and go against your conscience because God
lives in your heart and gives you power and grace to avoid and overcome
ALL temptation, within and without, to do what you know to be wrong.
That is what Jesus, and men like Him do, they live what they know to be
right for each and every moment. All men such as these are living
examples of what we are all capable of, and how we all should be.
